4.10	The_Hunter_(novel)	The Hunter (novel)	The Hunter (1962) is a crime thriller novel, written by Donald E. Westlake under the pseudonym Richard Stark. It was the basis for three feature films, John Boorman's Point Blank (1967), which starred Lee Marvin, Ringo Lam's Full Contact (1993), which starred Chow Yun-fat, and Payback (1999) which starred Mel Gibson. The book was adapted as a graphic novel by artist Darwyn Cooke in 2009.	
